summaries.short: In the Season One finale, Tony is stunned to learn who arranged the attempt on his life.
summaries.full: In the Season One finale, Tony is stunned to discover that the attempt on his life may have been ordered by someone very close to him. Later, he must deal with the fact that everyone knows he is seeing a shrink. Christopher is sent to take care of Jimmy Altieri.

summaries.short: Season Two opens with Tony adjusting to life in the aftermath of a federal crackdown.
summaries.full: Season Two opens with the aftermath of the federal crackdown: Junior's in jail, Melfi refuses to see Tony, Christopher's expanding into new business ventures, Pussy is still missing...and Tony's adjusting to life as the new boss. To complicate matters even more, Tony's free-spirited sister Janice arrives to take care of Livia.

summaries.short: Hit men are sent out to whack Tony, who comes out of his depression when he meets Isabella, an Italian exchange student.
summaries.full: Hit men are sent out to whack Tony, who comes out of his depression when he meets Isabella, an Italian exchange student staying next door.

summaries.short: Tony deals with protesters at a construction site. Meanwhile, Janice gets sucked into Livia's web.
summaries.full: When black protesters start picketing a construction company that used to be under Uncle Junior's control, Tony meets with the owner--as well as the leader of the protestors--to 'fix' the problem. Meanwhile, Janice gets sucked into Livia's web.

summaries.short: After Jimmy and Pussy are arrested in an FBI raid, Makazian tells Tony that Pussy may be wired for the Feds.
summaries.full: After Jimmy and Pussy are arrested in an FBI raid, Makazian tells a stunned Tony that Pussy may be wired for the Feds. Tony sends Paulie to find out for sure. Later, Tony learns that Makazian might be trying to frame Pussy to get out of his gambling debts.

summaries.full: Tony busts Meadow for partying at his mother's old house. Meanwhile, Ritchie Aprile is out of the can after ten years and looking for action--much to the chagrin of a local pizza-shop owner.
